 0020:     """Generates a time dependent contact matrix
 0021: 
 0022:     For prefactors :math:`a_{W1}, a_{W2}, a_{S1}, a_{S2}, a_{O1}, a_{O2}`
 0023:     that multiply the contact matrices CW, CS, and CO.
 0024:     the final contact matrix is computed as
 0025: 
 0026:     .. math::
 0027:         CM_{ij} = CH_{ij} + (a_{W1})_i CW_{ij} (a_{W2})_j
 0028:                     + (a_{S1})_i CW_{ij} (a_{S2})_j
 0029:                     + (a_{O1})_i CO_{ij} (a_{O2})_j
 0030: 
 0031:     For all the intervention functions, if a prefactor is passed as scalar,
 0032:     it is set to be an M (=no. of metapopulation groups) dimensional vector
 0033:     with all entries equal to the scalar.
 0034: 
 0035:     Parameters
 0036:     ----------
 0037:     CH: 2d np.array
 0038:         Contact matrix at home
 0039:     CW: 2d np.array
 0040:         Contact matrix at work
 0041:     CS: 2d np.array
 0042:         Contact matrix at school
 0043:     CO: 2d np.array
 0044:         Contact matrix at other locations
 0045:     """
 0046: 
 0047:     cdef:
 0048:         np.ndarray CH, CW, CS, CO

 0307:     """A class for generating a spatial compartmental model with commute data
 0308: 
 0309:     Let :math:`\\mu, \\nu` denote spatial index and i, j denote age group index.
 0310: 
 0311:     .. math::
 0312:         C^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} = \\frac{1}{N^\\mu_i} \widetilde{C}^{\\mu \\nu}_{ij}
 0313: 
 0314:     Parameters
 0315:     ----------
 0316:     b: float
 0317:         Parameter b in the above equation
 0318:     populations: np.array(n_loc, M)
 0319:         Populations of regions by age groups. Here n_loc is the number of regions
 0320:         and M is the number of age groups.
 0321:     areas: np.array(n_loc)
 0322:         Areas of the geographical regions.
 0323:     commutes: np.array(n_loc, n_loc, M)
 0324:         Each entry commute[mu, nu, i] needs to be the number of people of age
 0325:         group i commuting from :math:`\\mu` to :math:`\\nu`.
 0326:         Entries with :math:`\\mu = \\nu` are ignored.
 0327:     """
 0328:     cdef:

 0461:     """A class for generating a minimal spatial compartmental model
 0462: 
 0463:     Let :math:`\\mu, \\nu` denote spatial index and i, j denote age group index,
 0464: 
 0465:     .. math::
 0466:         C^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} = \\frac{1}{a_{ij}} k^{\\mu\\nu} g^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} f^{\\mu\\nu}_{ij} C_{ij}
 0467: 
 0468:     where
 0469:     .. math::
 0470:         a_{ij} = \sum_{\mu\nu} k^{\mu\nu}_{ij} g^{\mu\nu}_{ij} \sqrt{ \frac{ N_i^\mu N_j^\nu} {N_i N_j}}
 0471:         k^{\mu \nu} = \exp ( - b_{\mu\nu} | r^\mu - r^\nu |) \\
 0472:         b_{\mu, \nv} = (\rho^\mu \rho^\nu)^{-c} \\
 0473:         g^{\mu\nu}_{ij} = (\rho^\mu_i \rho^\nu_j)^b \\
 0474:         f^{\mu\nu}_{ij} = \sqrt{ \frac{N_i N_j^\nu}{N_i^\mu N_j}}
 0475: 
 0476:     where :math:`C_{ij}` is the non-spatial age structured contact matrix,
 0477:     :math:`\rho^\mu_i` is the population density of age group i
 0478:     in spatial location :math:`\mu`,
 0479:     :math:`\rho_i` is the total population density of age group i,
 0480:     :math:`r^\mu` is the spatial position of the :math:`\mu`th location,
 0481:     :math:`N_i^\mu` is the population of the age group i at :math:`\mu`,
 0482:     :math:`N_i` is the total population of the age group i,
 0483:     and b, c are free parameters
 0484: 
 0485:     Parameters
 0486:     ----------
 0487:     b: float
 0488:         Parameter b in the above equation.
 0489:     c: float
 0490:         Paramter c in the above equation.
 0491:     populations: np.array(n_loc, M)
 0492:         The population of each age group (total number of age group = M)
 0493:         in each location (total number of location = n_loc ).
 0494:     areas: np.array(n_loc)
